{"title_page": "List of number-one singles in Australia during the 1960s", "text_new": "{{Use Australian English|date=March 2015}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{infobox record charts}}\nThe following lists the number one singles on the Australian Singles Chart during the 1960s.\n\nThe source for this decade is the \"[[Kent Music Report]]\". These charts were calculated in the 1990s in retrospect, by [[David Kent (historian)|David Kent]], using archival data.\n\n{|class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"font-size:90%;\"\n|+Key\n!scope=row style=\"background-color: #FFFF99\" |The yellow background indicates the #1 song on the KMR End of Year Chart\n|-\n!scope=row style=\"background-color:lightblue\" |The light blue background indicates the #1 song on the KMR End of Decade Chart\n|}\n\n==1960==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! | Date\n! | Artist\n! | Single\n! | Weeks at number one\n|-\n|2 January\n|rowspan=5 align=\"center\"|[[Bill Haley & His Comets]]\n|rowspan=5 align=\"center\"|\"[[Joey's Song]]\" / \"[[Joey's Song|Ooh! Look-a-There, Ain't She Pretty?]]\"\n|rowspan=5 align=\"center\"| 8 weeks\n([[List of number-one singles in Australia during the 1950s#1959|3 weeks in Dec 1959]])\n|-\n|9 January\n|-\n|16 January\n|-\n|23 January\n|-\n|30 January\n|-\n|6 February\n|rowspan=2 align=\"center\"|[[Billy \"Crash\" Craddock|Crash Craddock]]\n|rowspan=2 align=\"center\"|\"[[Boom Boom Baby (song)|Boom Boom Baby]]\"\n|rowspan=2 align=\"center\"| 4 weeks\n|-\n|13 February\n|-\n|20 February\n|align=\"center\"|[[Johnny O'Keefe]] {{flagicon|Australia}}\n|align=\"center\"|\"She's My Baby\"\n|align=\"center\"| 1 week\n|-\n|27 February\n|rowspan=2 align=\"center\"|Crash Craddock\n|rowspan=2 align=\"center\"|\"Boom Boom Baby\"\n|rowspan=2 align=\"center\"| 4 weeks\n|-\n|5 March\n|-\n|12 March\n|rowspan=4 align=\"center\"|[[Emile Ford|Emile Ford and the Checkmates]]\n|rowspan=4 align=\"center\"|\"[[What Do You Want to Make Those Eyes at Me For?]]\"\n|rowspan=4 align=\"center\"| 4 weeks\n|-\n|19 March\n|-\n|26 March\n|-\n|2 April\n|-\n|9 April\n|rowspan=2 align=\"center\"|[[Johnny and the Hurricanes]]\n|rowspan=2 align=\"center\"|\"[[Jimmy Crack Corn (folk song)|Beatnik Fly]]\"\n|rowspan=2 align=\"center\"| 2 weeks\n|-\n|16 April\n|-\n|23 April\n|rowspan=4 align=\"center\"|[[Jim Reeves]]\n|rowspan=4 align=\"center\"|\"[[He'll Have to Go]]\"\n|rowspan=4 align=\"center\"| 4 weeks\n|-\n|30 April\n|-\n|7 May\n|-\n|14 May\n|-\n|21 May\n|align=\"center\"|[[Elvis Presley]]\n|align=\"center\"|\"[[Stuck on You (Elvis Presley song)|Stuck on You]]\" / \"Fame and Fortune\"\n|align=\"center\"| 1 week\n|-\n|28 May\n|rowspan=2 align=\"center\"|[[Lonnie Donegan|Lonnie Donegan and His Group]]\n|rowspan=2 align=\"center\"|\"[[My Old Man's a Dustman]]\"\n|rowspan=2 align=\"center\"| 2 weeks\n|-\n|4 June\n|-\n|11 June\n|rowspan=3 align=\"center\"|[[Rolf Harris]] {{flagicon|Australia}}\n|rowspan=3 align=\"center\"|\"[[Tie Me Kangaroo Down, Sport]]\"\n|rowspan=3 align=\"center\"| 3 weeks\n|-\n|18 June\n|-\n|25 June\n|-\n|2 July\n|rowspan=2 align=\"center\"|[[Bobby Rydell]]\n|rowspan=2 align=\"center\"|\"[[Swingin' School]]\" / \"[[Ding-A-Ling]]\"\n|rowspan=2 align=\"center\"| 2 weeks\n|-\n|9 July\n|-\n|16 July\n|rowspan=3 align=\"center\"|[[Connie Francis]]\n|rowspan=3 align=\"center\"|\"[[Everybody's Somebody's Fool]]\"\n|rowspan=3 align=\"center\"| 3 weeks\n|-\n|23 July\n|-\n|30 July\n|-\n|6 August\n|rowspan=2 align=\"center\"|[[Jimmie Rodgers (pop singer)|Jimmie Rodgers]]\n|rowspan=2 align=\"center\"|\"[[Just a Closer Walk with Thee]]\"\n|rowspan=2 align=\"center\"| 2 weeks\n|-\n|13 August\n|-\n|20 August\n|rowspan=4 align=\"center\"|[[The Beau Marks]]\n|rowspan=4 align=\"center\"|\"Clap Your Hands\"\n|rowspan=4 align=\"center\"| 4 weeks\n|-\n|27 August\n|-\n|3 September\n|-\n|10 September\n|-\n|17 September\n|rowspan=2 align=\"center\"|[[The Ventures]]\n|rowspan=2 align=\"center\"|\"[[Walk, Don't Run (song)|Walk, Don't Run]]\"\n|rowspan=2 align=\"center\"| 2 weeks\n|-\n|24 September\n|-\n|1 October\n|align=\"center\"|[[Johnny O'Keefe]] {{flagicon|Australia}}\n|align=\"center\"|\"Come on and Take My Hand\" / \"Don't You Know (Pretty Baby)\"\n|align=\"center\"| 1 week\n|-\n|8 October\n|rowspan=7 align=\"center\"|Elvis Presley\n|bgcolor=#FFFF99 rowspan=7 align=\"center\"|\"[[It's Now or Never (song)|It's Now or Never]]\"\n|rowspan=7 align=\"center\"| 7 weeks\n|-\n|15 October\n|-\n|22 October\n|-\n|29 October\n|-\n|5 November\n|-\n|14 November\n|-\n|19 November\n|-\n|26 November\n|rowspan=4 align=\"center\"|[[The Drifters]]\n|rowspan=4 align=\"center\"|\"[[Save the Last Dance for Me]]\"\n|rowspan=4 align=\"center\"| 4 weeks\n|-\n|3 December\n|-\n|10 December\n|-\n|17 December\n|-\n|24 December\n|rowspan=2 align=\"center\"|Elvis Presley\n|rowspan=2 align=\"center\"|\"[[Are You Lonesome Tonight? (song)|Are You Lonesome Tonight?]]\" / \"[[I Gotta Know]]\"\n|rowspan=2 align=\"center\"| 6 weeks\n|-\n|31 December\n|}\n\n'''Other hits'''<br />\nSongs peaking at number two included \"[[Running Bear]]\" by [[Johnny Preston]], \"If I Had a Girl\" by [[Rod Lauren]], \"[[What in the World's Come Over You]]\" by [[Jack Scott (singer)|Jack Scott]], \"[[Mule Skinner Blues]]\" by [[The Fendermen]], \"[[Itsy Bitsy Teenie Weenie Yellow Polkadot Bikini]]\" by [[Brian Hyland]], \"I Found a New Love\" / \"Defenceless\" by [[Lonnie Lee]], \"[[Please Don't Tease]]\" by [[Cliff Richard]] and [[The Shadows]], \"[[Peter Gunn (song)#Other versions|Peter Gunn]]\" by [[Duane Eddy]] and The Rebels, and \"[[North to Alaska]]\" by [[Johnny Horton]].\n\nOther hits (with their peak positions noted) were \"[[Teen Angel (song)|Teen Angel]]\" by [[Mark Dinning]] (3), \"[[Little Boy Lost (song)|Little Boy Lost]]\" by [[Johnny Ashcroft]] (3), \"[[Cathy's Clown]]\" by [[The Everly Brothers]] (3), \"What a Mouth (What a North and South)\" by [[Tommy Steele]] (3), \"[[When Will I Be Loved (song)|When Will I Be Loved]]\" / \"[[Be-Bop-A-Lula]]\" by [[The Everly Brothers]] (3), \"[[Let's Think About Living]] by [[Bob Luman]] (3), \"[[My Heart Has a Mind of Its Own]]\" / \"[[Malague\u00f1a (song)|Malaguena]]\" by [[Connie Francis]] (3), \"[[In The Mood]]\" by [[Ernie Fields]] (4), \"[[Handy Man (song)|Handy Man]]\" by [[Jimmy Jones (singer)|Jimmy Jones]] (4), \"[[Sink the Bismark]]\" by [[Johnny Horton]] (4), \"A Kookie Little Paradise\" by [[Jo Ann Campbell]] (4), \"[[Volare (song)#Recorded cover versions|Volare]]\" / \"I'd Do it Again\" by [[Bobby Rydell]] (4), \"Yes Sir That's My Baby\" by [[Col Joye]] & The Joy Boys (5), \"Greenfields\" by [[The Brothers Four]] (5), and \"[[I'm Sorry (Brenda Lee song)|I'm Sorry]] by [[Brenda Lee]] (6).\n\nHits by Australasian artists included \"(Making Love on A) Moonlit Night\" by [[Col Joye]], \"Turn the Lights Out, Johnny\" / \"Koala Bear\" by [[Johnny Devlin]] and The Devils with The Delltones, and \"Do You Love Me\"/\"Whiplash\" by [[Robie Porter|Rob E.G.]]\n\n==1961==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! | Date\n! | Artist\n! | Single\n! | Weeks at number one\n|-\n|7 January\n|rowspan=4 align=\"center\"|[[Elvis Presley]]\n|rowspan=4 align=\"center\"|\"[[Are You Lonesome Tonight? (song)|Are You Lonesome Tonight?]]\" / \"[[I Gotta Know]]\"\n|rowspan=4 align=\"center\"| 6 weeks\n|-\n|14 January\n|-\n|21 January\n|-\n|28 January\n|-\n|4 February\n|rowspan=3 align=\"center\"|[[Bert Kaempfert|Bert Kaempfert and His Orchestra]]\n|rowspan=3 align=\"center\"|\"[[Wonderland by Night]]\"\n|rowspan=3 align=\"center\"| 3 weeks\n|-\n|11 February\n|-\n|18 February\n|-\n|25 February\n|rowspan=3 align=\"center\"|[[Bobby Vee]]\n|rowspan=3 align=\"center\"|\"[[Rubber Ball]]\"\n|rowspan=3 align=\"center\"| 3 weeks\n|-\n|4 March\n|-\n|11 March\n|-\n|18 March\n|align=\"center\"|[[Billy \"Crash\" Craddock|Crash Craddock]]\n|align=\"center\"|\"One Last Kiss\"\n|align=\"center\"| 1 week\n|-\n|25 March\n|rowspan=7 align=\"center\"|[[Elvis Presley]]\n|rowspan=4 align=\"center\"|\"[[Wooden Heart]]\"\n|rowspan=4 ali