equests'' (EP): \"[[Long Tall Sally]]\" / \"[[Boys (The Shirelles song)|Boys]]\" / \"[[I Call Your Name]]\"\n|align=\"center\"| 1 week\n|-\n|11 July\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=2|[[Cilla Black]]\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=2|\"[[You're My World]]\"\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=2| 2 weeks\n|-\n|18 July\n|-\n|25 July\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=11|[[The Beatles]]\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=6|\"[[A Hard Day's Night (song)|A Hard Day's Night]]\" / \"[[Things We Said Today]]\"\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=6| 6 weeks\n|-\n|1 August\n|-\n|8 August\n|-\n|15 August\n|-\n|22 August\n|-\n|29 August\n|-\n|5 September\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=5|\"[[I Should Have Known Better]]\" / \"[[If I Fell]]\"\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=5| 5 weeks\n|-\n|12 September\n|-\n|19 September\n|-\n|26 September\n|-\n|3 October\n|-\n|10 October\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=2|[[Roy Orbison]]\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=2|\"[[Oh, Pretty Woman|Pretty Woman]]\"\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=2| 2 weeks\n|-\n|17 October\n|-\n|24 October\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=2|[[The Honeycombs]]\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=2|\"[[Have I the Right?]]\"\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=2| 2 weeks\n|-\n|31 October\n|-\n|7 November\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=2|[[Ray Columbus & the Invaders|Ray Columbus and the Invaders]]\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=2|\"She's a Mod\"\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=2| 2 weeks\n|-\n|14 November\n|-\n|21 November\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=3|[[Elvis Presley]]\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=3|\"[[Ain't That Lovin' You, Baby|Ain't That Loving You, Baby]]\" / \"Ask Me\"\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=3| 3 weeks\n|-\n|28 November\n|-\n|5 December\n|-\n|12 December\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=3|[[The Beatles]]\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=3|\"[[I Feel Fine]]\" / \"[[She's a Woman]]\"\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=3| 8 weeks\n|-\n|19 December\n|-\n|26 December\n|-\n|}\n\n'''Other hits'''<br />\nSongs peaking at number two included \"[[Secret Love (Doris Day song)#Kathy Kirby version|Secret Love]]\" by [[Kathy Kirby]], \"[[A World Without Love]]\" by [[Peter & Gordon]], \"[[My Boy Lollipop#The Millie Small version|My Boy Lollipop]]\" by [[Millie (singer)|Millie]], \"[[Wishin' and Hopin']]\" by [[Dusty Springfield]], \"[[The House of the Rising Sun#The Animals' version|The House of the Rising Sun]]\" by [[The Animals]], \"[[Do Wah Diddy Diddy#Manfred Mann version|Do Wah Diddy Diddy]]\" by [[Manfred Mann]], \"[[William Tell (opera)#Recordings|William Tell Overture]]\" by [[Sounds Incorporated]], and \"[[When You Walk in the Room#The Searchers version|When You Walk in the Room]]\" by [[The Searchers (band)|The Searchers]].\n\nOther hits (with their peak positions noted) were \"[[Dominique]]\" by [[The Singing Nun]] (3), \"[[Twenty Four Hours from Tulsa]]\" by [[Gene Pitney]] (3), \"[[Don't Talk to Him]]' by [[Cliff Richard]] (3), \"[[Glad All Over]]\" by [[The Dave Clark Five]] (3), \"[[Diane (1927 song)|Diane]]\" by [[The Bachelors]] (3), \"[[Suspicion (Terry Stafford song)|Suspicion]]\" by [[Terry Stafford]] (3), \"Poision Ivy\" / Broken Things\" by [[Billy Thorpe and the Aztecs]] (3), \"[[Rag Doll (The Four Seasons song)|Rag Doll]]\" by [[The Four Seasons (band)|The Four Seasons]] (3), \"[[Such a Night]]\" by [[Elvis Presley]] (3), \"[[You Don't Own Me]]\" by [[Lesley Gore]] (4), \"[[Needles and Pins (song)|Needles and Pins]]\" by [[The Searchers (band)|The Searchers]] (4), \"[[Bits and Pieces (song)|Bits and Pieces]]\" / \"All of the Time\" by [[The Dave Clark Five]] (4), \"[[Viva Las Vegas (song)|Viva Las Vegas]]\" / \"[[What'd I Say#Legacy|What'd I Say]]\" by [[Elvis Presley]] (4), [[Twist and Shout (EP)|''Twist and Shout'' EP]] by [[The Beatles]] (5), \"Hangin' Five\" by [[The Delltones]] (5), \"[[Hello, Dolly! (song)|Hello, Dolly!]]\" by [[Louis Armstrong]] (5), and \"[[It Hurts to Be in Love]]\" by [[Gene Pitney]] (6).\n\nHits by Australasian artists included \"The Crusher\" by [[The Atlantics]], \"When You're Not to Wear\" by [[Rob E.G.]], \"She Wears My Ring\" / \"Let's Love Tonight\" by 