 (song)|Eve of Destruction]]\" by [[Barry McGuire]], \"[[What's New Pussycat? (song)|What's New Pussycat?]]\" by [[Tom Jones (singer)|Tom Jones]], \"Sing C'est La Vie\" by [[Sonny & Cher]], and \"[[Yesterday (Beatles song)|Yesterday]]\" / \"[[Act Naturally#The Beatles version|Act Naturally]]\" by [[The Beatles]].\n\nOther hits (with their peak positions noted) were \"[[Leader of the Pack]]\" by [[The Shangri-Las]] (3), \"Do What You Do Do Well\" by [[Ned Miller]] (3), \"[[It's Not Unusual]]\" by [[Tom Jones (singer)|Tom Jones]] (3), \"[[Can't You Hear My Heartbeat]]\" / \"Silhouettes\" by [[Herman's Hermits]] (3), \"Paper Tiger\" by [[Sue Thompson]] (3), \"[[Mr. Tambourine Man#The Byrds' version|Mr. Tambourine Man]]\" by [[The Byrds]] (3), \"[[She's So Fine]]\" / \"The Old Oak Tree\" by [[The Easybeats]] (3), \"Fool, Fool, Fool\" by [[Ray Brown & The Whispers]] (3), \"[[Unchained Melody#The Righteous Brothers version|Unchained Melody]]\" by [[The Righteous Brothers]] (3), \"[[I Got You Babe]]\" by [[Sonny & Cher]] (3), \"Tell Him I'm Not Home\" / \"Call on Me\" by [[Normie Rowe]] (3), \"[[Ringo (song)|Ringo]]\" by [[Lorne Greene]] (4), \"[[Goldfinger (Shirley Bassey song)|Goldfinger]]\" by [[Shirley Bassey]] (4), \"[[The Hucklebuck]]\" by [[Brendan Bowyer]] (4), \"[[If You Gotta Go, Go Now]]\" by [[Manfred Mann]] (4), \"[[You've Lost That Lovin' Feelin']]\" by [[The Righteous Brothers]] (5), \"[[Heart of Stone (The Rolling Stones song)|Heart of Stone]]\" / \"Heart of Stone\" by [[The Rolling Stones]] (5), \"It Ain't Nessearly So\" by [[Normie Rowe]] (5), \"Walk Away (Warum Nur Warum)\" by [[Matt Monro]] (6), \"Goodbye\" by [[Roy Orbison]] (6), and \"[[Like a Rolling Stone]]\" by [[Bob Dylan]] (7).\n\nHits by Australasian artists included \"Velvet Waters\" by Tony Worsley, \"[[Wedding Ring (song)|Wedding Ring]]\" by [[The Easybeats]], \"Morning Town Ride\" by [[The Seekers]], and \"Rockin' Robin\" / \"Baby What's Wrong\" by The Henchmen.\n\n==1966==\n{| class=\"wikit