=4|\"[[The Ballad of John and Yoko]]\"\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=4| 4 weeks\n|-\n|19 July\n|-\n|26 July\n|-\n|2 August\n|-\n|9 August\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=4|[[Elvis Presley]]\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=4|\"[[In the Ghetto]]\"\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=4| 4 weeks\n|-\n|16 August\n|-\n|23 August\n|-\n|30 August\n|-\n|6 September\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=5|[[The Rolling Stones]]\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=5|\"[[Honky Tonk Women]]\"\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=5| 5 weeks\n|-\n|13 September\n|-\n|20 September\n|-\n|27 September\n|-\n|4 October\n|-\n|11 October\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=3|[[Russell Morris]] {{flagicon|Australia}}\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=3|\"Part Three into Paper Walls\" / \"The Girl That I Love\"\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=3| 3 weeks\n|-\n|18 October\n|-\n|25 October\n|-\n|1 November\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=2|[[Ross D. Wyllie]] {{flagicon|Australia}}\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=2|\"The Star\"\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=2| 2 weeks\n|-\n|8 November\n|-\n|15 November\n|align=\"center\"|The Beatles\n|bgcolor=#FFFF99 align=\"center\"|\"[[Something (Beatles song)|Something]]\" / \"[[Come Together]]\"\n|align=\"center\"| 5 weeks\n|-\n|22 November\n|align=\"center\"|[[Roy Orbison]]\n|align=\"center\"|\"Penny Arcade\"\n|align=\"center\"| 1 week\n|-\n|29 November\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=4|The Beatles\n|bgcolor=#FFFF99 align=\"center\" rowspan=4|\"Something\" / \"Come Together\"\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=4| 5 weeks\n|-\n|6 December\n|-\n|13 December\n|-\n|20 December\n|-\n|27 December\n|align=\"center\"|[[Elvis Presley]]\n|align=\"center\"|\"[[Suspicious Minds]]\"\n|align=\"center\"| 3 weeks ([[List of number-one singles in Australia during the 1970s|2 weeks in Jan. 1970]])\n|-\n|}\n\n'''Other hits'''<br />\nSongs peaking at number two included \"[[Love Child (song)|Love Child]]\" by [[Diana Ross and The Supremes]], \"[[Going Up the Country]]\" by [[Canned Heat]], \"[[Build Me Up Buttercup]]\" by [[The Foundations]], \"[[If I Can Dream]]\" / \"[[Edge of Reality (song)|Edge of Reality]]\" by [[Elvis Presley]], \"[[Dizzy (Tommy Roe song)|Dizzy]]\" by [[Tommy Roe]], \"[[Goodbye (Mary Hopkin song)|Goodbye]]\" by [[Mary Hopkin]], and \"[[In the Year 2525]]\" by [[Zager and Evans]].\n\nOther hits (with their peak positions noted) were \"[[Crimson and Clover]]\" by [[Tommy James and the Shondells]] (3), \"[[Gitarzan]]\" by [[Ray Stevens]] (3), \"[[Bad Moon Rising]]\" by [[Creedence Clearwater Revival]] (3), \"[[My Sentimental Friend]]\" by [[Herman's Hermits]] (3), \"[[A Boy Named Sue]]\" by [[Johnny Cash]] (3), \"[[Something in the Air]]\" by [[Thunderclap Newman]] (3), \"[[Sweet Caroline]]\" by [[Neil Diamond]] (3), \"Star-Crossed Lovers\" by [[Neil Sedaka]] (4), \"[[Aquarius/Let the Sunshine In]]\" by [[The 5th Dimension]] (4), \"[[One (Harry Nilsson song)|One]]\" by [[John Farnham|Johnny Farnham]] (4), \"[[Indian Giver (song)|Indian Giver]]\" by [[1910 Fruitgum Company]] (5), \"[[Proud Mary]]\" by [[Credence Clearwater Revival]] (5), \"[[Dear Prudence#Cover versions|Dear Prudence]]\" by [[Doug Parkinson]] (5), \"[[Spinning Wheel (song)|Spinning Wheel]]\" by [[Blood, Sweat & Tears]] (5), \"[[All Along the Watchtower#The Jimi Hendrix Experience|All Along the Watchtower]]\" by [[The Jimi Hendrix Experience]] (6), \"[[Give Peace a Chance]]\" by [[The Plastic Ono Band]] (6), \"[[Sugar, Sugar]]\" by [[The Archies]] (6).\n\nHits by Australasian artists included \"[[Saved by the Bell (song)|Saved by the Bell]]\" by [[Robin Gibb]], \"[[Don't Forget to Remember]]\" by [[The Bee Gees]],   \"La La\" by [[The Flying Circus (band)|The Flying Circus]], \"Try to Remember\" by [[New World (band)|New World]], and  \"Such a Lovely Way\" by [[The Groop]].\n\n==See also==\n*[[Music of Australia]]\n*[[List of UK Singles Chart number ones of the 1960s]]\n*[[List of Billboard number-one singles]]\n*[[Lists of UK Singles Chart number ones]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n*[http://www.austchartbook.com.au David Kent's Australian Chart 