 Angel]]\" by [[Mark Dinning]] (3), \"[[Little Boy Lost (song)|Little Boy Lost]]\" by [[Johnny Ashcroft]] (3), \"[[Cathy's Clown]]\" by [[The Everly Brothers]] (3), \"What a Mouth (What a North and South)\" by [[Tommy Steele]] (3), \"[[When Will I Be Loved (song)|When Will I Be Loved]]\" / \"[[Be-Bop-A-Lula]]\" by [[The Everly Brothers]] (3), \"[[Let's Think About Living]] by [[Bob Luman]] (3), \"[[My Heart Has a Mind of Its Own]]\" / \"[[Malague\u00f1a (song)|Malaguena]]\" by [[Connie Francis]] (3), \"[[In The Mood]]\" by [[Ernie Fields]] (4), \"[[Handy Man (song)|Handy Man]]\" by [[Jimmy Jones (singer)|Jimmy Jones]] (4), \"[[Sink the Bismark]]\" by [[Johnny Horton]] (4), \"A Kookie Little Paradise\" by [[Jo Ann Campbell]] (4), \"[[Volare (song)#Recorded cover versions|Volare]]\" / \"I'd Do it Again\" by [[Bobby Rydell]] (4), \"Yes Sir That's My Baby\" by [[Col Joye]] & The Joy Boys (5), \"Greenfields\" by [[The Brothers Four]] (5), and \"[[I'm Sorry (Brenda Lee song)|I'm Sorry]] by [[Brenda Lee]] (6).\n\nHits by Australasian artists included \"(Making Love on A) Moonlit Night\" by [[Col Joye]], \"Turn the Lights Out, Johnny\" / \"Koala Bear\" by [[Johnny Devlin]] and The Devils with The Delltones, and \"Do You Love Me\"/\"Whiplash\" by [[Robie Porter|Rob E.G.]]\n\n==1961==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! | Date\n! | Artist\n! | Single\n! | Weeks at number one\n|-\n|7 January\n|rowspan=4 align=\"center\"|[[Elvis Presley]]\n|rowspan=4 align=\"center\"|\"[[Are You Lonesome Tonight? (song)|Are You Lonesome Tonight?]]\" / \"[[I Gotta Know]]\"\n|rowspan=4 align=\"center\"| 6 weeks\n|-\n|14 January\n|-\n|21 January\n|-\n|28 January\n|-\n|4 February\n|rowspan=3 align=\"center\"|[[Bert Kaempfert|Bert Kaempfert and His Orchestra]]\n|rowspan=3 align=\"center\"|\"[[Wonderland by Night]]\"\n|rowspan=3 align=\"center\"| 3 weeks\n|-\n|11 February\n|-\n|18 February\n|-\n|25 February\n|rowspan=3 align=\"center\"|[[Bobby Vee]]\n|rowspan=3 align=\"center\"|\"[[Rubber Ball]]\"\n|rowspan