\"\n|rowspan=2 align=\"center\"| 2 weeks\n|-\n|28 October\n|-\n|4 November\n|rowspan=3 align=\"center\"|[[Roy Orbison]]\n|rowspan=3 align=\"center\"|\"[[Crying (Roy Orbison song)|Crying]]\" / \"Candy Man\"\n|rowspan=3 align=\"center\"| 3 weeks\n|-\n|11 November\n|-\n|18 November\n|-\n|25 November\n|rowspan=2 align=\"center\"|[[James Darren]]\n|rowspan=2 align=\"center\"|\"[[Goodbye Cruel World (James Darren song)|Goodbye, Cruel World]]\"\n|rowspan=2 align=\"center\"| 2 weeks\n|-\n|2 December\n|-\n|9 December\n|rowspan=4 align=\"center\"|[[Charlie Drake]]\n|rowspan=4 align=\"center\"|\"[[My Boomerang Won't Come Back]]\"\n|rowspan=4 align=\"center\"| 6 weeks\n|-\n|16 December\n|-\n|23 December\n|-\n|30 December\n|-\n|}\n\n'''Other hits'''<br />\nSongs peaking at number two included \"[[Calcutta (song)|Calcutta]]\" by [[Lawrence Welk]], \"[[Wheels (The String-A-Longs song)|Wheels]]\" by [[The String-A-Longs]], \"Theme From [[Exodus (1960 film)|Exodus]]\" by [[Ferrante & Teicher]], \"[[A Hundred Pounds of Clay]]\" by [[Gene McDaniels]], \"[[Hats Off to Larry]]\" by [[Del Shannon]], \"[[Together (1928 song)#Recorded versions|Together]]\" by [[Connie Francis]], and \"[[(Marie's the Name) His Latest Flame]]\" / \"[[Little Sister (Elvis Presley song)|Little Sister]]\" by [[Elvis Presley]].\n\nOther hits (with their peak positions noted) were \"[[Sway (Luis Demetrio song)|Sway]]\" by [[Bobby Rydell]] (3), \"[[Calendar Girl (song)|Calendar Girl]]\" by [[Neil Sedaka]] (3), \"[[Good Time Baby]]\" / Cheri\u00e9 by [[Bobby Rydell]] (3), \"[[Little Devil]]\" by [[Neil Sedaka]] (3), \"[[Baby Face (1926 song)|Baby Face]]\" and \"[[Take Good Care of My Baby]]\" by [[Bobby Vee]] (3), \"[[Hit The Road Jack]]\" by [[Ray Charles]] (3), \"[[Corrine, Corrina]]\" by [[Ray Peterson]] (4), \"[[Will You Love Me Tomorrow]]\" by [[The Shirelles]] (4), \"[[Blue Moon (1934 song)|Blue Moon]]\" by [[The Marcels]] (4), \"[[Moody River]]\" by [[Pat Boone]] (4), \"Smoky Mokes\" by The Joy Boys (4), \"[[Where the Boys Are]]\" by [[Connie Francis]] (5), \"[[Running Scared (Roy Orbison song)|Running Scared]]\" / \"[[Love Hurts#Roy Orbinson version|Love Hurts]]\" by [[Roy Orbison]] (5), \"[[You're Sixteen]]\" by [[Johnny Burnette]] (6), and \"[[I've Told Every Little Star#Linda Scott version|I've Told Every Little Star]]\" by [[Linda Scott]] (6).\n\nHits by Australasian artists included \t\n\"Ready for You\" / \"Save the Last Dance for Me\" by [[Johnny O'Keefe]], \"Six White Boomers\" by [[Rolf Harris]], \"Got a Zack in the Back of Me Pocket\" by [[Johnny Devlin]] and The Bricks with The Deeners, and \"Goin' Steady\" / \"Naughty Girls\" [[Col Joye]] and The Joy Boys.\n\n==1962==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! | Date\n! | Artist\n! | Single\n! | Weeks at number one\n|-\n|6 January\n|rowspan=2 align=\"center\"|[[Charlie Drake]]\n|rowspan=2 align=\"center\"|\"[[My Boomerang Won't Come Back]]\"\n|rowspan=2 align=\"center\"| 6 weeks\n|-\n|13 January\n|-\n|20 January\n|align=\"center\"|[[Sandy Nelson]]\n|align=\"center\"|\"[[Let There Be Drums]]\"\n|align=\"center\"| 1 week\n|-\n|27 January\n|rowspan=5 align=\"center\"|[[Elvis Presley]]\n|rowspan=5 align=\"center\"|\"[[Can't Help Falling in Love]]\" / \"[[Rock-A-Hula Baby]]\"\n|rowspan=5 align=\"center\"| 5 weeks\n|-\n|3 February\n|-\n|10 February\n|-\n|17 February\n|-\n|24 February\n|-\n|3 March\n|rowspan=3 align=\"center\"|[[Bobby Darin]]\n|rowspan=3 align=\"center\"|\"Multiplication\" / \"Irresistible You\"\n|rowspan=3 align=\"center\"| 3 weeks\n|-\n|10 March\n|-\n|17 March\n|-\n|24 March\n|align=\"center\"|[[Acker Bilk|Mr Acker Bilk]]\n|align=\"center\"|\"[[Stranger on the Shore]]\"\n|align=\"center\"| 1 week\n|-\n|31 March\n|align=\"center\"|[[Dion DiMucci|Dion]]\n|align=\"center\"|\"[[The Wanderer (Dion song)|The Wanderer]]\"\n|align=\"center\"| 1 week\n|-\n|7 April\n|align=\"center\"|[[Kenny Ball|Kenny Ball and His Jazzmen]]\n|align=\"center\"|\"[[Moscow Nights|Midnight in Moscow]]\"\n|align=\"center\"| 1 week\n|-\n|14 