 You to Want Me\" by [[The Shadows]] (3), \"[[Wipe Out (instrumental)|Wipe Out]]\" / \"Surfer Joe\" by [[The Surfaris]] (3), \"[[She Loves You]]\" / \"[[I'll Get You]]\" by [[The Beatles]] (3), \"[[Come a Little Bit Closer]]\" by [[The Delltones]] (4), \t\n\"Jezebel\" / \"Stage to Cimarron\" by [[Rob E.G.]] (4), \"[[Blue Velvet (song)#Bobby Vinton version|Blue Velvet]]\" by [[Bobby Vinton]] (4), \"Little Band of Gold\" by [[James Gilreath]] (5), \"[[Mar\u00eda Elena (song)#Cover versions|Mar\u00eda Elena]]\" by [[Los Indios Tabajaras]] (5), \"[[Ruby Baby]]\" by [[Dion DiMucci]] (6), and \"[[I Like It (Gerry and the Pacemakers song)|I Like It]]\" by [[Gerry and the Pacemakers]] (6).\n\nHits by Australasian artists included \"(And Her Name is) Scarlet\" by [[Leo de Kroo|The De Kroo Brothers]], and \"Proud of You\" by Jay Justin.\n\n==1964==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! | Date\n! | Artist\n! | Single\n! | Weeks at number one\n|-\n|4 January\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=23|[[The Beatles]]\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=6|\"[[I Want to Hold Your Hand]]\"\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=6| 7 weeks\n|-\n|11 January\n|-\n|18 January\n|-\n|25 January\n|-\n|1 February\n|-\n|8 February\n|-\n|15 February\n|bgcolor=#FFFF99 align=\"center\" rowspan=7|\"[[I Saw Her Standing There]]\" / \"[[Love Me Do]]\"\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=7| 7 weeks\n|-\n|22 February\n|-\n|29 February\n|-\n|7 March\n|-\n|14 March\n|-\n|21 March\n|-\n|28 March\n|-\n|4 April\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=2|\"[[Roll Over Beethoven]]\" / \"[[Hold Me Tight]]\"\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=2| 2 weeks\n|-\n|11 April\n|-\n|18 April\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=3|[[All My Loving (EP)|''All My Loving'' EP]] \n|align=\"center\" rowspan=3| 3 weeks\n|-\n|25 April\n|-\n|2 May\n|-\n|9 May\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=5|\"[[Can't Buy Me Love]]\" / \"[[You Can't Do That]]\"\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=5| 5 weeks (and a sixth on 27 June)\n|-\n|16 May\n|-\n|23 May\n|-\n|30 May\n|-\n|6 June\n|-\n|13 June\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=2|[[Mary Wells]]