center\" rowspan=2|\"[[Snoopy's Christmas]]\"\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=2| 2 weeks\n|-\n|30 December\n|-\n|}\n\n'''Other hits'''<br />\nSongs peaking at number two included  \"[[When I Was Young (song)|When I Was Young]]\" by [[Eric Burdon and The Animals]], \"[[Puppet on a String]]\" by [[Sandie Shaw]], \"[[San Francisco (Be Sure to Wear Flowers in Your Hair)]]\" by [[Scott McKenzie]], \"[[Itchycoo Park]]\" by [[Small Faces]], and \"[[Massachusetts (Bee Gees song)|Massachusetts]]\" by [[Bee Gees]].\n\nOther hits (with their peak positions noted) were \"[[The Happening (song)|The Happening]]\" by [[The Supremes]] (3),<ref>{{cite web |url=https://books.google.nl/books?id=wycEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA53&dq|title=Billboard Magazine, July 8, 1967 |work=Billboard}}</ref> \"It's Not Easy\" by [[Normie Rowe]] (3), \"[[Let's Spend The Night Together]]\" / \"[[Ruby Tuesday (song)|Ruby Tuesday]]\" by [[The Rolling Stones]] (3), \"[[Release Me (1949 song)#Engelbert Humperdinck version|Release Me]]\" by [[Engelbert Humperdinck (singer)|Engelbert Humperdinck]] (3), \"[[Dedicated to the One I Love#The Mamas & The Papas version|Dedicated to the One I Love]]\" by [[The Mamas & The Papas]] (3), \"[[Groovin']]\" by [[The Young Rascals]] (3), ''The Monkees Volume 1'' EP by [[The Monkees]] (3), \"The Two of Us\" by [[Jackie Trent]] and [[Tony Hatch]] (3), \"When Will I Be Loved?\" / \"Kiss Me Now\" by [[Johnny Young]] and Kompany (4), \"[[Happy Jack (song)|Happy Jack]]\" by [[The Who]] (4), \"[[A Little Bit Me, a Little Bit You]]\" / \"[[The Girl I Knew Somewhere]]\" by [[The Monkees]] (4), \"[[Waterloo Sunset]]\" by [[The Kinks]] (4), \"[[In the Chapel in the Moonlight#Cover versions|In the Chapel in the Moonlight]]\" by [[Dean Martin]] (4), \"[[The Letter (Box Tops song)|The Letter]]\" by [[The Box Tops]] (4), \"Pamela Pamela\" by [[Wayne Fontana]] (5), \"[[There's a Kind of Hush]]\" by [[Herman's Hermits]] (5), \"[[Silence Is Golden (song)|Silence Is Golden]]\" by [[The Tremeloes]] (5), \"Lightning's Girl\" by [[Nancy Sinatra]] (5), \"[[Gimme Some Lovin']]\" by [[The Spencer Davis Group]] (6), and \"[[To Love Somebody (song)|To Love Somebody]]\" by [[Bee Gees]] (6).\n\nHits by Australasian artists included \"[[Living in a Child's Dream]]\" by [[The Masters Apprentices]], \"What's Wrong with the Way I Live\" / \"9.50\" by [[The Twilights]], \"Woman You're Breaking Me\" by [[The Groop]], \"Heaven and Hell\" / \"Pretty Girl\"  by [[The Easybeats]], and \"What Am I Doing Here With You?\" by [[Bev Harrell]].\n\n==1968==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! | Date\n! | Artist\n! | Single\n! | Weeks at number one\n|-\n|6 January\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=2|[[The Beatles]]\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=2|\"[[Hello, Goodbye]]\" / \"[[I Am the Walrus]]\"\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=2| 2 weeks\n|-\n|13 January\n|-\n|20 January\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=6|[[John Farnham]] {{flagicon|Australia}}\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=6|\"[[Sadie (The Cleaning Lady)]]\"\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=6| 6 weeks\n|-\n|27 January\n|-\n|3 February\n|-\n|10 February\n|-\n|17 February\n|-\n|24 February\n|-\n|2 March\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=2|[[John Fred|John Fred and His Playboy Band]]\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=2|\"[[Judy in Disguise (With Glasses)|Judy in Disguise]]\"\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=2| 2 weeks\n|-\n|9 March\n|-\n|16 March\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=5|[[Paul Mauriat|Paul Mauriat and His Orchestra]]\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=5|\"[[L'amour est bleu|Love Is Blue]]\"\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=5| 5 weeks\n|-\n|23 March\n|-\n|30 March\n|-\n|6 April\n|-\n|13 April\n|-\n|20 April\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=2|The Beatles\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=2|\"[[Lady Madonna]]\" / \"[[The Inner Light (song)|The Inner Light]]\"\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=2| 2 weeks\n|-\n|27 April\n|-\n|4 May\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=5|[[Bobby Goldsboro]]\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=5|\"[[Honey (Bobby Goldsboro song)|Honey]]\"\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=5| 5 weeks\n|-\n|11 May\n|-\n|18 May\n|-\n|25 May\n|-\n|1 June\n